@0 = ~Welcome, noble <SIRMAAM>, to Barun's Smithy. I, of course, am Barun, master dwarven smith and creator of fine magical items. How may I be of service to you today?~
@1 = ~What exactly is it you do here?~
@2 = ~I want you to make an item for me.~
@3 = ~I'll be going now.~
@4 = ~I'm a weapon and armor smith, of sorts. I take component items and combine them with magic items to make objects of even greater majesty and power. Not a bad little gig, if you can get it. If you want I can look through your inventory and backpack to see if you have anything I can combine into a powerful weapon or suit of armor. Is there anything in particular you want me to look for?~ 
@5 = ~I'm interested in axes and armor.~
@6 = ~I'm interested in blunt and crushing weapons.~
@7 = ~I'm interested in magical swords.~
@8 = ~I'm interested in some of the less common weapons.~
@9 = ~What kinds of things would 'component' items be?~
@10 = ~I'm not interested right now.~
@11 = ~Okay, I see there's some stuff on my anvil. Let me take a look and see what I can construct for you.~
@12 = ~Just place one component item and one magical weapon or one suit of magic armor on the forge and I'll help you out. But if the forge isn't full - like now - I can't really do my thing, can I?~
@13 = ~Good day to you then, <SIRMAAM>.~ 
@14 = ~Here you go, just take this book I have here. It will explain everything you can make and the components required to do so.~
@15 = ~Look, you've already got a copy of my recipe book, so what more do you want? Just read the damn thing.~
@16 = ~So, axes and armor is it? Let me just take a look at what you've got in that pack of yours and I'll give you a list of what I can make from your inventory. If an item isn't on the list, you don't have the stuff I need to make it. Just pick something you're interested in having me make.~ 
@17 = ~Chromatic Breastplate: Requires ritellium and full plate armor.~ 
@18 = ~Scales of Truth: Requires special holy water and a suit of magical armor of total AC 5.~
@19 = ~Whitebone Leather Armor: Requires a gargoyle skull and studded leather armor +2 with AC 5.~ 
@20 = ~Sentinel: Requires adamantite and a battleaxe +1.~ 
@21 = ~Stonefire Great Axe: Requires adamantite and a halberd +1.~ 
@22 = ~Dragon Horror: Requires dragon blood and battleaxe +1~
@23 = ~I don't have the required ingredients.~ 
@24 = ~Clubs, maces and hammers for you, eh? I'll just take a look at your stuff and see what we've got to work with, then I'll give you a list of the items I can make for you. If an item isn't on the list, you don't have the stuff I need to make it. Just pick something you're interested in having me make.~ 
@25 = ~Gladiator's Club: Requires Ironwood and a regular club.~
@26 = ~Ironwood Mace: Requires ironwood and a mace +1.~ 
@27 = ~Stormhammer: Requires ritellium and warhammer +1.~ 
@28 = ~Foundation Flail: Requires ironwood and flail +1.~ 
@29 = ~Mace of Disruption: Requires special holy water and a mace +1.~
@30 = ~Drone Morning Star: Needs fairy dust and a a morningstar +1.~ 
@31 = ~Rune Hammer: Requires adamantite and a war hammer +2.~ 
@32 = ~Nothing beats a good old sword, does it? Tried and true. Okay, let me peek inside your backpack and I'll give you a list of the wondrous blades I can make from the stuff in your inventory. If an item isn't on the list, you don't have the stuff I need to make it. Just pick something you're interested in having me make.~ 
@33 = ~Harbinger Kin Greatsword: Requires adamantite and a two-handed sword +1.~
@34 = ~Sword Saint Katana: Requires adamantite and a katana +1.~ 
@35 = ~Astral Blade Longsword: Requires ritellium and a longsword +1.~
@36 = ~Astral Blade Bastard sword: Requires ritellium and a bastard sword +1.~ 
@37 = ~Desert Wind Scimitar: Requires adamantite and a scimitar +1.~
@38 = ~Feyduster Short Sword: Requires Fairy Dust and a short sword +1.~ 
@39 = ~Of course. Not everybody's into axes, swords and maces now, are they? Let me give you a list of the exotic weapons I can make with the items in your pack. If an item isn't on the list, you don't have the stuff I need to make it. Just pick something you're interested in having me make.~ 
@40 = ~Ravager Halberd: Requires dragon blood and a halberd +2.~ 
@41 = ~Fey Spear: Requires fairy dust and a spear +1.~ 
@42 = ~Let's see... you have a diamond and a suit of magical armor. I could build you a Chromatic Breastplate - a fine suit of armor if I do say so myself. But it won't be cheap. It will cost 7000 gold pieces for me to make this for you. Payment in advance, of course.~ 
@43 = ~Here is your 7000 gold.~ 
@44 = ~I cannot afford this item.~
@45 = ~Nevermind, I don't want you to make the item.~
@46 = ~What is that? Some special holy water? Powerful stuff. I could combine it with your suit of magical armor and make you a Scales of Truth suit. But this job isn't cheap. It will cost 6000 gold pieces for me to make this for you. Payment in advance, of course.~ 
@47 = ~Here is your 6000 gold.~
@48 = ~Hmmm... I could combine that gargoyle skull and your suit of magical armor into a top of the line suit of Whitebone Armor. But this job isn't cheap. It will cost 5000 gold pieces for me to make this for you. Payment in advance, of course.~ 
@49 = ~Here is your 5000 gold.~ 
@50 = ~That adamantite could be worked into that magic battleaxe to make a Sentinel. Fine weapon. Mighty fine weapon. But this job isn't cheap. It will cost 5500 gold pieces for me to make this for you. Payment in advance, of course.~ 
@51 = ~Here is your 5500 gold.~ 
@52 = ~Your adamantite and magic axe will make a two-handed ax of stone fire. But this job isn't cheap. It will cost 6000 gold pieces for me to make this for you. Payment in advance, of course.~ 
@53 = ~Dragon blood is powerful stuff. If I remember right I could combine it with that magic hand axe and make a Dragon Horror. But it won't be cheap. It will cost 8000 gold pieces for me to make this for you Payment in advance, of course.~ 
@54 = ~Here is your 8000 gold.~ 
@55 = ~Ironwood. You know, I could combine the ironwood with that magic club of yours and make you a Gladiator's club. But this job isn't cheap. It will cost 4000 gold pieces for me to make this for you. Payment in advance, of course.~
@56 = ~Here is your 4000 gold.~ 
@57 = ~Interesting. Ironwood would graft quite nicely to that magical mace to make a solid Ironwood Mace. But this job isn't cheap. It will cost 5000 gold pieces for me to make this for you. Payment in advance, of course.~ 
@58 = ~You know, this ritellium can be combined with a magical hammer, and make a beautiful Stormhammer. But this job isn't cheap. It will cost 7000 gold pieces for me to make this for you. Payment in advance, of course.~ 
@59 = ~This ironwood and magic flail will make an excellent Foundation flail. But this job isn't cheap. It will cost 6000 gold pieces for me to make this for you. Payment in advance, of course.~
@60 = ~Aha - jackpot! I can use your special holy water and your magic mace to create a Mace of Disruption! But this job isn't cheap. It will cost 6000 gold pieces for me to make this for you. Payment in advance, of course.~
@61 = ~Look at that - fairy dust! I could combine it with your magic morning star to construct a Drone Morning Star. But this job isn't cheap. It will cost 6500 gold pieces for me to make this for you. Payment in advance, of course.~ 
@62 = ~Here is your 6500 gold.~ 
@63 = ~Okay - I can take your adamantite and your magic war hammer make you a Rune Hammer. But this job isn't cheap. It will cost 6500 gold pieces for me to make this for you. Payment in advance, of course.~
@64 = ~Ah... there's real potential here. Your adamantite and your magic greatsword will make a Harbinger Kin Greatsword. But this job isn't cheap. It will cost 6000 gold pieces for me to make this for you. Payment in advance, of course.~ 
@65 = ~Okay, here's something. I can use your adamantite and your magic katana to make a Sword Saint Katana. But this job isn't cheap. It will cost 6000 gold pieces for me to make this for you. Payment in advance, of course.~ 
@66 = ~This is interesting. By adding your ritellium to your magic longsword I can make an Astral Blade Longsword. But this job isn't cheap. It will cost 6500 gold pieces for me to make this for you. Payment in advance, of course.~
@67 = ~Interesting. By adding your ritellium to the magic bastard sword, we get the Astral Blade Bastard sword. But this job isn't cheap. It will cost 6500 gold pieces for me to make this for you. Payment in advance, of course.~
@68 = ~I could forge that adamantite with that magic scimitar and make you a Desert Wind Scimitar. But this job isn't cheap. It will cost 5500 gold pieces for me to make this for you. Payment in advance, of course.~
@69 = ~You know, I could use that fairy dust and your magic short sword to make you a Feyduster short sword. But this job isn't cheap. It will cost 5500 gold pieces for me to make this for you. Payment in advance, of course.~ 
@70 = ~Huh. Dragon blood. Not going to ask where you got that, but I can use it to turn that magic halberd into a Ravager Halberd. But this job isn't cheap. It will cost 6000 gold pieces for me to make this for you. Payment in advance, of course.~ 
@71 = ~Hmmm... that fairy dust will work into your magic spear. I could make a Fey Spear, if you want. But this job isn't cheap. It will cost 6000 gold pieces for me to make this for you. Payment in advance, of course.~ 
@72 = ~Always a pleasure doing business with a fine <MANWOMAN> such as yourself. Stand back - you don't want to catch a hammer in the head.~
@73 = ~Fair enough - but this isn't a charity I'm running. If you don't have the gold, you don't get the item.~
@74 = ~Fair enough - a customer always has the right to change <HISHER> mind.~
@75 = ~Excellent choice. When you're ready, just place the component and appropriate magic item on the forge then come speak to me again.~
@76 = ~There you go, <SIRMAAM>. Quick as you please and the job is done. You can pick the item up from my forge.~
